==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alder fly
<hw>Al"der fly</hw></mhw>. <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Any of numerous dark-colored neuropterous insects of the genus
<gen>Sialis</gen> or allied genera. They have predaceous aquatic
larv⟦ae⟧, which are used for bait.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Angling)</fld> <def>An artificial fly with brown
mottled wings, body of peacock harl, and black legs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alder-liefest</ent>⟦br⟧
